<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="534" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1648,1999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1829,1855]" pageId="3" pageNumber="534">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[376,424,1829,1855]" pageId="3" pageNumber="534">type</typeStatus>
series was collected when the official name of the town was Grahamstown, the locality reflected in the labels on the 
<typeStatus box="[487,535,1865,1891]" pageId="3" pageNumber="534">type</typeStatus>
series. The town has since been officially renamed Makhanda so that the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1865,1891]" pageId="3" pageNumber="534">type</typeStatus>
locality is Makhanda, East 
<collectingRegion box="[455,515,1901,1927]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="3" pageNumber="534">Cape</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[527,673,1901,1927]" name="South Africa" pageId="3" pageNumber="534">South Africa</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="534" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1648,1999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1937,1963]" pageId="3" pageNumber="534">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sanborn &amp; Villet" authorityYear="2020" box="[458,603,1937,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Afromelampsalta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteofasciata">
<emphasis box="[458,603,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="534">luteofasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a combination of 
<emphasis box="[829,896,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="534">luteus</emphasis>
(L. yellow) and 
<emphasis box="[1082,1182,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="534">fasciatus</emphasis>
(L. banded, striped) in reference to the yellow fasciae on the thorax and abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
